MBOMBELA &#8211; In the book The Silent Giants of Southern Africa by Bob Preller, a few unusual facts about elephants are explained in detail. It is a guide full of anecdotes, information about elephants and the people working for their conservation. Preller formerly worked in the financial sector but has been an honorary ranger for more than 40 years. His love for elephants started when he had to take care of an elephant calf when she was orphaned. In his book he writes about the elephant impact on plant life, the question of culling, their social habits and early elephant care.